data.title: 1940) – Find a Grave Gedenkstätte
data.meta_description: Sher Singh died at the age of 40, executed by hanging at the Pentonville Prison in London, England. He was sometimes referred to as Shaheed-I-Azam-Sardar-Udham-Sing. He was an Indian Revolutionary who had assassinated Michael O'Dwyer, the Governor of Punjab, India, who supported the Jallianwalla Bagh Massacre, where...
